As we continue to mold Enron Net Works into the service organization model discussed at the ENW All Employee meeting on Oct. 5, we are pleased to announce the following changes to the organization.

Steve Hotte, currently transitioning into the role of CIO for Enron Americas, will take responsibility for the following areas:
Gas Trading - Zhiyong Wei 
Power Trading - Steve Nat 
Back Office - Ramesh Rao 
Commercial Coordination - Tommy Yanowski 

John Paskin, currently transitioning into role of CIO for Corporate Systems will lead the following teams:
ISC - Allan Sommer 
Enterprise Portal - Tony Mends 
Treasury - Tom Conley 
Intranet/Livelink/Graphics - Scott Cleverly, JoAnne Knodel, Vikki McCullough 
CRM Strategy - Kevin Guion 
Matrix with HRIS - Kathy Schultea 

Steve Stock will move into the new role of Enterprise Frameworks reporting to Mark Pickering and will lead the following teams: 
Architecture - John Simmons 
Development Support - Richard Burchfield 
Global Data - Joe Wong 
MKM - Arlene Ogden 
Enterprise RAC 
 	 RAC Analytics - Winston Jia 
  	 RAC Infrastructure - Ramesh Ganapathy 
Global Valuation - Dana Docherty 

Interviews for a CIO for EGS are currently in progress. 

Please join us in congratulating all of these individuals on their new responsibilities.  A copy of the Organization structure is attached for your review. 

Greg, Sally and Mark

 